{
  "texts": [
    "• YACLC (Wang et al, 2021b).",
    "Multiple universities collaborate to create the YACLC dataset, featuring Chinese text samples.",
    "Graduate students specializing in pertinent fields are enlisted to assess the acceptability of Chinese sentences, contributing annotations for both correction and fluency.",
    "Corrections involve grammatical adjustments to align sentences with Chinese grammar standards, whereas fluency annotations focus on refining sentences for improved smoothness and authenticity, in accordance with prevalent Chinese communication norms.",
    "YACLC finds practical utility in tasks like grammar correction and text proofreading."
  ]
}